replies.body:
Xerath isn't a champion that is good at roaming. If Zed goes roam turbo push the lane and try to take the tower before he returns. That is the price he plays for roaming from a losing lane.

The big issue is "our jungle wasn't warded". Well time to go fix that...{{item:2055}} 

On more mobile midlanes right from the start of the game (especially when you are winning lane) you can start stepping away from the lane to ward, just keep the enemy midlaner on thier toes and worried you have gone roaming. But you are actually warding i preparation for when you will actually roam.
